# OpenAI Responses API - Request & Response Format

## Authentication & Headers

Same as Chat Completions:
```
Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY
Content-Type: application/json
```

Endpoint: `POST https://api.openai.com/v1/responses`

---

## 1. Request Body Structure

### Basic Request

```json
{
  "model": "gpt-5",
  "input": "string or array of input items",
  "tools": [],
  "tool_choice": "auto",
  "instructions": "optional system-level instructions",
  "reasoning": { "effort": "low" | "medium" | "high" },
  "include": ["web_search_call.action.sources"],
  "previous_response_id": "resp_abc123"
}
```

### Input Formats

**Simple string input:**
```json
{
  "input": "What was a positive news story from today?"
}
```

**Structured message array input:**
```json
{
  "input": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What was a positive news story from today?"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Multi-part content (text + images):**
```json
{
  "input": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "input_text",
          "text": "Describe this image"
        },
        {
          "type": "input_image",
          "image_url": "https://example.com/image.png"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Tool Definitions

#### Function Tool
```json
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "description": "Get the current weather for a location",
      "parameters": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "location": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "City and state, e.g. San Francisco, CA"
          },
          "unit": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["celsius", "fahrenheit"]
          }
        },
        "required": ["location"]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Web Search Tool (full options)
```json
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "web_search",
      "search_context_size": "low" | "medium" | "high",
      "user_location": {
        "type": "approximate",
        "country": "GB",
        "city": "London",
        "region": "London",
        "timezone": "Europe/London"
      },
      "filters": {
        "allowed_domains": [
          "pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov",
          "clinicaltrials.gov",
          "www.who.int"
        ]
      },
      "external_web_access": true
    }
  ]
}
```

Key notes from the docs:
- `filters` supports up to 100 URLs in the allow-list
- "When formatting URLs, omit the HTTP or HTTPS prefix"
- `external_web_access: false` runs in "offline/cache‑only mode"
- `user_location` uses two-letter ISO country codes and IANA timezones
- "user location is not supported for deep research models"

#### Web Search Preview Tool (legacy)
```json
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "web_search_preview"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Multi-turn with previous_response_id

```json
{
  "model": "gpt-5",
  "input": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Follow-up question here"
    }
  ],
  "previous_response_id": "resp_abc123def456"
}
```

### Sending Function Call Results Back

When the model returns a function_call output, you send results back as input items:

```json
{
  "model": "gpt-5",
  "input": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What's the weather in London?"
    },
    {
      "type": "function_call",
      "id": "fc_abc123",
      "call_id": "call_abc123",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "arguments": "{\"location\": \"London, UK\"}"
    },
    {
      "type": "function_call_output",
      "call_id": "call_abc123",
      "output": "{\"temperature\": 15, \"condition\": \"cloudy\"}"
    }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "description": "Get weather",
      "parameters": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "location": { "type": "string" }
        },
        "required": ["location"]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## 2. Response Body Structure

### Top-level Response Object

```json
{
  "id": "resp_67c9fa0502748190b7dd390736892e10",
  "object": "response",
  "created_at": 1741214213,
  "model": "gpt-5",
  "status": "completed",
  "output": [],
  "output_text": "The full text output concatenated...",
  "usage": {
    "input_tokens": 150,
    "output_tokens": 320,
    "total_tokens": 470,
    "input_tokens_details": {
      "cached_tokens": 0
    },
    "output_tokens_details": {
      "reasoning_tokens": 0
    }
  },
  "metadata": {},
  "temperature": 1.0,
  "top_p": 1.0,
  "max_output_tokens": null,
  "previous_response_id": null,
  "reasoning": { "effort": "medium" },
  "tools": [],
  "tool_choice": "auto"
}
```

### Output Array Item Types

#### Web Search Call Output Item
```json
{
  "type": "web_search_call",
  "id": "ws_67c9fa0502748190b7dd390736892e100be649c1a5ff9609",
  "status": "completed",
  "action": {
    "type": "search",
    "queries": ["positive news today March 2025"],
    "sources": [
      {
        "url": "https://example.com/article",
        "title": "Article Title",
        "snippet": "Brief excerpt..."
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

The `action` field has three types based on the docs:
- `"search"` — "represents a web search" with optional `queries`
- `"open_page"` — "represents a page being opened. Supported in reasoning models"
- `"find_in_page"` — "represents searching within a page. Supported in reasoning models"

Note: `sources` only appear when you pass `"include": ["web_search_call.action.sources"]`.

#### Function Call Output Item
```json
{
  "type": "function_call",
  "id": "fc_67c9fa0502748190b7dd3907",
  "call_id": "call_67c9fa0502748190b7dd3907",
  "name": "get_weather",
  "arguments": "{\"location\": \"London, UK\"}",
  "status": "completed"
}
```

#### Message Output Item (with annotations/citations)
```json
{
  "id": "msg_67c9fa077e288190af08fdffda2e34f20be649c1a5ff9609",
  "type": "message",
  "status": "completed",
  "role": "assistant",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "output_text",
      "text": "On March 6, 2025, several news...",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "type": "url_citation",
          "start_index": 2606,
          "end_index": 2758,
          "url": "https://example.com/article",
          "title": "Article Title"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Complete Response Example (Web Search)

```json
{
  "id": "resp_67c9fa0502748190",
  "object": "response",
  "created_at": 1741214213,
  "model": "gpt-5",
  "status": "completed",
  "output": [
    {
      "type": "web_search_call",
      "id": "ws_67c9fa0502748190b7dd390736892e100be649c1a5ff9609",
      "status": "completed"
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_67c9fa077e288190af08fdffda2e34f20be649c1a5ff9609",
      "type": "message",
      "status": "completed",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "output_text",
          "text": "On March 6, 2025, several news...",
          "annotations": [
            {
              "type": "url_citation",
              "start_index": 2606,
              "end_index": 2758,
              "url": "https://...",
              "title": "Title..."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "output_text": "On March 6, 2025, several news...",
  "usage": {
    "input_tokens": 150,
    "output_tokens": 320,
    "total_tokens": 470
  }
}
```

---

## 3. Key Differences from Chat Completions

| Aspect | Chat Completions | Responses API |
|--------|-----------------|---------------|
| Endpoint | `/v1/chat/completions` | `/v1/responses` |
| Auth | Same `Bearer` token | Same `Bearer` token |
| Input format | `messages` array with `role`/`content` | `input` (string or array) |
| Multi-turn | Manually pass full message history | Use `previous_response_id` |
| Web search | Requires special models (`gpt-4o-search-preview`) with `web_search_options` | Any compatible model + `tools: [{"type": "web_search"}]` |
| Tool results | `tool` role messages | `function_call_output` input items matched by `call_id` |
| Response structure | `choices[0].message.content` | `output` array + `output_text` convenience field |
| Domain filtering | Not available | `filters.allowed_domains` (up to 100) |
| Sources | Not available | Via `include: ["web_search_call.action.sources"]` |
| Live access control | Not available | `external_web_access: true/false` |

